    • getOneOf

      @Nullable public List<UserSchemaAttributeEnum> getOneOf()
      Non-empty array of valid JSON schemas. Okta only supports `oneOf` for specifying display names for an `enum`. Each schema has the following format: ``` { \"const\": \"enumValue\", \"title\": \"display name\" } ```json When `enum` is used in conjunction with `oneOf`, you must keep the set of enumerated values and their order. ``` {\"enum\": [\"S\",\"M\",\"L\",\"XL\"], \"oneOf\": [ {\"const\": \"S\", \"title\": \"Small\"}, {\"const\": \"M\", \"title\": \"Medium\"}, {\"const\": \"L\", \"title\": \"Large\"}, {\"const\": \"XL\", \"title\": \"Extra Large\"} ] } ```json The `oneOf` key is only supported in conjunction with `enum` and provides a mechanism to return a display name for the `enum` value.
      Returns:
      oneOf
